channel.title: Eclipse
channel.description: Well i recently got my linux laptop with Fedora installed and i need to know how would i install Eclipse or Netbeans on it. If anyone could offer light on this it would be appreciated because i'm not much of a linux user but i want to continue to develop things and i don't want to always have to use my windows computer.

item.title: Eclipse
item.dc:creator: @HcoJustin HcoJustin
item.description:
@HcoJustin wrote:

[quote=“Aetoc, post:14, topic:414636”][quote author=ziplock link=topic=516598.msg3751585#msg3751585 date=1316057454]

Did you do manual partitions? If so, you may have set it up wrong.

I had someone else setup everything for me, how would i allow it more space?

You can use the Disk Utility and check out your partitions. You can also modify them from there.
[/quote]

Oh ok i’ll do that.[/quote]

They should be clearly labled as to what is supposed to be mounted on each partition. If you can’t tell, running df in a terminal will tell you some more info about the paritions, and what is mounted where.

IE. You’ll get some output similar to this

/dev/hda2 28G 7.6G 19G 29% / tmpfs 252M 0 252M 0% /lib/init/rw tmpfs 252M 0 252M 0% /dev/shm /dev/hda1 464M 37M 403M 9% /boot /dev/hda3 8.3G 429M 7.5G 6% /var nfs6:/home 520G 461G 60G 89% /home mirrors:/mirrors 1.4T 1.1T 233G 83% /mirrors /dev/mapper/big-phat 77G 36G 42G 46% /space mailstore:/var/mail 9.9G 4.8G 4.7G 51% /var/mail

Obviously the filesystem’s wouldn’t be labeled exactly the same, but far left column is the FS, far right column is where it’s mounted at.
